
[1]muller

   MUL'LER, n. [L. molaris, from mola, a mill-stone.]

   1. A stone held in the hand with which colors and other matters are
   ground on another stone; used by painters and apothecaries.

   2. An instrument used by glass grinders, being a piece of wood with the
   piece of glass to be ground cemented to one end, either convex in a
   basin, or concave in a sphere or bowl.
